---------------------------------------------------
--- SubVehicle Shield Manager
--- Author: Louis-A.A 
--- Description:
---  This script is made to be plug and play. It manages the position of held subvehicles (ON TURRETS) to protect the construct.
---------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------
--- NOTES AND INSTRUCTIONS
------------------------------------------------------
--- GENERAL SETUP
------------------------------------------------------
---
---The script will crash if there are empty holders on turrets on INIT. avoid this.
---
---The program has an INIT phase that allows you to build, change or add/remove drones. 
---This in turn requires saving and reloading the vehicle afterwards.
---
--- This script controls subvehicles mounted on turrets
--- (component type 7) to create a defensive drone shield.
---
--- Drones are positioned between the construct and incoming
--- threats. The wall is dynamically regenerated every update
--- cycle, allowing drones to react to changing targets and
--- missile threats.
---
--- The script is designed to be plug-and-play, but proper
--- turret placement is important for optimal performance.
------------------------------------------------------

-----------------------------------------------------
---DRONE REQUIREMENTS
-----------------------------------------------------
-- the drone does not require an AI
-- the drone can be any size or shape

--ALL HOLDERS ON TURRETS MUST HAVE A DRONE

------------------------------------------------------
--- HOLDER / TURRET CONFIGURATION
------------------------------------------------------
--- 1) DO NOT USE ROLL IN HOLDER SETTINGS.
---    Roll cannot be accessed or modified through Lua.
---    Only azimuth and elevation are controlled.
---
--- 2) Place drone holders close to the center of mass (COM)
---    of the construct.
---
---    Good placement:
---      - Spread around the COM
---      - Similar distance from the center
---      - Clear line of movement
---
---    Bad placement:
---      - Holders located on extreme ends of the craft
---      - Holders blocked by armor or other subobjects
--- 
--- 3) it gets expotentionally more computationaly expensive the more drones you have, 
--- so try to keep it reasonable yeah?
--- 
---
--- The wall position is calculated using the furthest holder
--- from the threat direction. This ensures the shield remains
--- flat and prevents drones from forming a curved surface.
------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------
--- WEAPON PLACEMENT
------------------------------------------------------
--- Avoid placing weapons directly around drone holders.
---
--- The script automatically creates firing holes in the
--- drone wall to allow weapons to shoot through.
---
--- Weapons very close to holders may create large permanent
--- gaps in the shield and reduce protection.
---
--- For best results:
---   - Place offensive weapons away from shield holders
---   - Leave clear firing lanes
---   - Use dedicated shield areas on the craft
------------------------------------------------------
